UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2492
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION urging the United States Department of Defense and the
2 federal government to protect the earned benefits of our veterans from retaliatory and
3 punitive measures.
4 WHEREAS, the people of Kentucky recognize and celebrate the patriotic service
5 and community contributions of the more than 370,000 Kentucky veterans and their
6 families, totaling over one million residents, who call our great Commonwealth their
7 home; and
8 WHEREAS, in recognition of their vital contribution to our state economy and
9 local communities, we voice full support for the preservation and protection of their
10 earned benefits from any punitive elimination or reduction of their retiree pay, veteran
11 healthcare, or disability compensation for any exercise of their First Amendment right of
12 free speech; and
13 WHEREAS, Kentucky veterans have faithfully served the nation and we steadfastly
14 honor their service by protecting their honorably earned benefits; and
15 WHEREAS, any punitive risk that unjustly threatens Kentucky veterans' benefits
16 would severely impact our 370,000 veterans and their families, who represent 25 percent
17 of our population; and
18 WHEREAS, threats to recall any veteran into active duty for the purpose of
19 conducting a court martial to downgrade or eliminate justly earned benefits sets a
20 dangerous precedent for any and all veterans stating that their earned benefits could be
21 subject to arbitrary and capricious administrative action by the United States Department
22 of Defense or the United States Department of Veterans Affairs; and
23 WHEREAS, protected First Amendment speech doesn't require agreement to be
24 protected, and its exercise should never be used against a person to threaten, intimidate,
25 or provoke action. Retaliatory threats against protected speech are a valid concern that
26 warrants action from the Commonwealth to protect its veterans; and
27 WHEREAS, to disenfranchise one veteran can disenfranchise all veterans;
Page 1 of 2
