UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2492
1 NOW, THEREFORE,
2 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. The General Assembly hereby urges the United States Department of
4 Defense and the United States Department of Veterans Affairs to protect the earned
5 benefits of veterans now and into the future from retaliatory and punitive political action.
6 Section 2. The General Assembly stands with our military veterans in
7 advocating for their right to free speech and the protection of their earned retirement,
8 healthcare, and disability benefits from specious claims.
9 Section 3. The General Assembly condemns any course of action that would
10 deny or revoke earned military benefits unjustly for political gain.
11 Section 4. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit
12 copies of this Resolution to Representative Pamela Stevenson and to the Kentucky
13 congressional delegation.
